text: Grevillea costata is a shrub of the genus Grevillea native to an area along the west coast of the Mid West region of Western Australia. The shrub is spreading with many branches and typically grows to a height of in height and has non-glaucous branchlets that are angular and ridged and sericeous between ridges. ==See also== * List of Grevillea species ==References== costata Category:Proteales of Australia Category:Eudicots of Western Australia
